vstore.framework.communication.download.events

Class DownloadProgressEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • vstore.framework.communication.download.events.DownloadProgressEvent

  • public class DownloadProgressEvent
extends java.lang.Object
    This event gets published regularly during a file download. Contains the progress in percent as well as the request id and the file id. Also contains a flag to check if the download is done. Will be published in sticky mode, so you have to remove it from the event bus with EventBus.getDefault().removeStickyEvent(event).

      • DownloadProgressEvent

        public DownloadProgressEvent(java.lang.String fileID,
                             java.lang.String requestID,
                             int progress,
                             boolean done,
                             java.net.URI fileUri,
                             MetaData meta)
        Constructs a new DownloadProgressEvent object.
        Parameters:
        fileID - The uuid of the file for which the progress is reported.
        requestID - If necessary, you can provide an ID to identify the request later on.
        progress - The download progress in percent.
        done - A flag that indicates if the download has finished.
        fileUri - The file object representing the file that has been downloaded. Should only be set if the progress is 100% and done is true.
        meta - The metadata for the download.
